                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#124v" facs="127"> f. 124v, col. 2, bottom</locus>, Six lines of <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2915RepCh196">Malkǝʾ-hymn to
                                                  Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</title>, with incipit
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                          ሰላም፡ ለኵልያቲከ፡ [ወ]ለንዋየ፡ [ው]ስጥከ።እንግልጋ፡ [ለ]ኅንብርትከ፡ ሰላም፡ ወለሐቌከ፡ ጸዋረ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>
                        </foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                          Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#7r #11v #37v #66v #73r" facs="009 014 040 069 075">folss. 7r, 11v, 37v, 66v, 73r, </locus>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#23r #50r" facs="025 052">23r, 50r, </locus>);
                          erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#5v #9v #17r #92v" facs="008 012 019 095">5v, 9v, 17r, 92v</locus>, etc.)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                          This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for
                          the width of most lines. Occasionally a line is too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line
                          (e.g., <locus target="#25v #36v #45v #46r" facs="028 039 046 048">fols. 25v, 36v, 45v, 46r</locus>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

